<article>
    <h1>Mea&#xAD;sures to raise aware&#xAD;ness Pro&#xAD;grammes for se&#xAD;condary schools, col&#xAD;leges and uni&#xAD;ver&#xAD;si&#xAD;ties</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201219/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-19"><time>2020-12-19</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Re­sources and ac­tiv­i­ties for pre-schools and pri­mary schools</p>
    <p>To en­cour­age re­spon­si­ble pet own­er­ship from a young age, the An­i­mal and Vet­eri­nary Ser­vice (AVS) is putting on plays about an­i­mal wel­fare for pre-school­ers. All pre-school cen­tres will get new books about pet care by March and re­source kits for early child­hood ed­u­ca­tors in the sec­ond quar­ter of next year.</p>
    <p>Ed­u­ca­tional dis­play pan­els are to be loaned out from the AVS to both preschools and pri­mary schools to teach pupils how to look af­ter pets. They will be sup­ple­mented by online ac­tiv­ity sheets. Pri­mary 4 pupils will also get 40,000 pa­per mod­els teach­ing them about the sci­ence be­hind an­i­mal be­hav­iour.</p>
    <p>2</p>
    <p>Stu­dents can ex­pect trips to AVS cen­tres such as the Sem­bawang An­i­mal Quar­an­tine Sta­tion, where they can watch how quar­an­tined pets are cared for.</p>
    <p>The AVS is also work­ing with groups such as St John Sin­ga­pore on in­tro­duc­ing hu­man-an­i­mal in­ter­ac­tion to their badge pro­grammes. Those at in­sti­tutes of higher learn­ing will also have the chance to pro­pose prac­ti­cal so­lu­tions on an­i­mal-re­lated is­sues as part of fi­nal-year pro­jects.</p>
    <p>3</p>
    <p>Free we­bi­nars for the pub­lic</p>
    <p>Mem­bers of the pub­lic will have more op­por­tu­ni­ties to learn about pet be­hav­iour through free monthly we­bi­nars on an­i­mal health, wel­fare and be­hav­iour from to­day. AVS vets and pro­fes­sion­als from the pet industry will fea­ture in th­ese ses­sions, which will be held on every fourth Satur­day of the month.</p>
    <p>4</p>
    <p>Vol­un­teer­ing op­por­tu­ni­ties for in­di­vid­u­als and firms</p>
    <p>The AVS is cre­at­ing more vol­un­teer­ing op­por­tu­ni­ties through an­i­mal-re­lated pro­grammes. Fol­low­ing pi­lot ses­sions last month with a youth out­reach pro­gramme run by Fei Yue Com­mu­nity Ser­vices, it will con­duct in­ter­ven­tions for more youth to boost their well-be­ing with the help of an­i­mals.</p>
    <p>5</p>
    <p>Up­dates on pet sec­tor re­view</p>
    <p>The AVS is en­hanc­ing the wel­fare of pets through mea­sures such as one-time li­cens­ing for ster­ilised dogs in­tro­duced in Septem­ber.</p>
    <p>The Re­hom­ing and Adop­tion Work Group was also started by the AVS in Oc­to­ber to im­prove th­ese prac­tices.</p>


</article>

